race.comment: RELIABLE JO (11) took a sit at Tatura and was only beaten 1.2L over 1980m. Lightly raced and draws for the run of the race. Peaks and shapes as a solid each way play. MICKIO (1) continues to improve and this is easier than his placed effort at Murtoa last time. Lugs top weight, but winning rider Rawiller is reunited and will likely push forward from an outside gate. Tough to beat with average luck in the run. WHISKY MOON (2) was tried at Stakes level before the spell and is sure to improve off his first-up outing at a mile. TAVISTOCK DANCER (8) is a leader who has been winning by big margins at short odds. Goes up in weight but maps to advantage. Will give a big sight again.
